{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "femvalidate", "icon": "SOP/femvalidate", "since": "18.5", "tags": "FEM Solver, FEM Hybrid Object, FEM Solid Object", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["FEM Validate"], "extent": [142, 159]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Visualizes the quality of a tetrahedral mesh."], "extent": [159, 213]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["To achieve the best results and the best performance with FEM, it is important that your input mesh is ", {"type": "em", "text": ["good quality"]}, ". A mesh is good quality when its tetrahedrons resemble regular tetrahedrons and its triangles resemble equilateral triangles. A good quality mesh should also have no inverted tetrahedrons."], "extent": [213, 521]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["FEM Validate SOP"]}, " allows you to check your initial geometry before you send it to an FEM simulation. This node lets you:"], "extent": [521, 649]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Visualize the qualities of the primitives in your simulation mesh using color gradations between red (poor quality) and green (good quality)."], "extent": [649, 793]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Inspect the simulation mesh and identify any bad tetrahedrons, bad triangles, or inverted (according to the winding order used by Houdini) tetrahedrons on the outside ", {"type": "em", "text": ["or"]}, " inside of your simulation mesh."], "extent": [793, 1000]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["With this quality feedback, you can eliminate or improve poor quality tets by adjusting the settings of upstream nodes like the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/nodes/sop/remesh", "type": "link", "text": ["Remesh SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/remesh"}, ", ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/nodes/sop/tetconform", "type": "link", "text": ["Tet Conform SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/tetconform"}, ", and the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/nodes/sop/tetembed", "type": "link", "text": ["Tet Embed SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/tetembed"}, ". "], "extent": [1000, 1248]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["When importing a tetrahedral mesh from another package, its winding order may be the opposite to the one used by Houdini. If you encounter this, then you can use a ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/nodes/sop/reverse", "type": "link", "text": ["Reverse SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/reverse"}, " to correct the mesh\u2019s winding order."], "extent": [1248, 1483]}, {"type": "video_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "video", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1483, 1491], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 4, "text": ["Example: Quality visualization of a tetrahedral mesh"], "extent": [1545, 1609]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"src": "/videos/fem_validatesop.mp4", "loop": "true"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1609, 1621], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Group"], "extent": [1621, 1629], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Limit the geometry that is to be validated to this group."], "extent": [1629, 1692]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Type"], "extent": [1692, 1698], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Allow choice between visualization of mesh quality and tet inversions."], "extent": [1698, 1774]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["View Slice"], "extent": [1774, 1786], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Look at a slice of the tet mesh to see the tets on the interior."], "extent": [1786, 1856]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Quality"], "extent": [1856, 1870], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Quality Threshold"], "extent": [1870, 1894], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["A quality threshold value between 0 and 1; All tets and polygons below this value will be colored red, all above are colored green."], "extent": [1894, 2035]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Isolate Primitives Below Threshold"], "extent": [2035, 2075], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Show only the primitives below the specified quality threshold."], "extent": [2075, 2148]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Inversion"], "extent": [2148, 2164], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Position Type"], "extent": [2164, 2184], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The position attribute used to determine whether a tet is inverted:\n        Material means that the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["materialP"]}, " attribute is used. Current means that the current position attribute ", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, " is used."], "extent": [2184, 2387]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Isolate Inverted"], "extent": [2387, 2409], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Show only the primitives that are inverted."], "extent": [2409, 2462]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Slice Settings"], "extent": [2462, 2483], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Origin"], "extent": [2483, 2496], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The origin of the clipping plane."], "extent": [2496, 2535]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Distance"], "extent": [2535, 2545], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The distance of the clipping plane from the origin in the direction of the normal."], "extent": [2545, 2633]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Direction"], "extent": [2633, 2644], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The normal direction of the clipping plane."], "extent": [2644, 2699]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}], "text": "Parameters"}], "title": ["FEM Validate"], "summary": ["Visualizes the quality of a tetrahedral mesh."]}